text: It's been moving & humbling this week to see the brave students from Parkland become so active, but the reality is that parents should be able to take their children to school each morning knowing that they will come home safely that night. This epidemic should not be happening.

I'll be on the air with Mark & Dave today at 3:15 and 5:15. Be sure to tune in to 1190 KEX for a little drive time fun!
This AM I stopped in to meet w/members of the Clack Co. Econ Dev Comm to disc econ dev & a path forward for the co. & state.
Visited McKesson’s Wilsonville pharmaceutical dist. facility today. Impressive operation and great employer with 110 hard working Oregonians
Just met w/the Clackamas County Business Alliance. Great opp to disc localissues & get feedback.
Today, we #Remember911 and honor the victims, families, first responders & service members that have sacrificed so much for our country.
This pm I was able to tour CAPACES in Woodburn. The new building is impressive & will serve as a hub for a # of organizations.
This pm Rep. Komp & I held a town hall @ Country Meadows Village. It was a great opp for us to disc local issues & get feedback.
I’ll be on KGW News Channel 8 tomorrow night for Straight Talk with Laurel Porter. Be sure to tune in at 6:30.
I was pleased to participate in a Alzheimer's forum @ Salem Hospital this pm. I heard a lot of great ideas & plan on taking back to DC.
Visited the OR State Fair, site of so much OR history. Susan B. Anthony visit in 1871, JFK visit in 1960 and today, the two foot corn dog
This am I sat down to meet w/OR hunger advocates. In July, I advocated for OR families by standing up against further reductions in SNAP.
Disc campaign fin w/ Move to Amend. I've intro a constitutional amend that would ensure that the voice of the maj remains > the $ of a few.
Last weekend 17 students graduated from Springdale Jobs Corps. Congrats to all & good luck w/ your future endeavors.
This PM I was honored to speak @ the Alaska Air PDX-DCA Inaugural Reception. New non-stop flight opens economic doors starting tomorrow AM.
Just met w/Matt Perry @ Big Dog Coffee to disc issues impt to our soldiers. They deserve the best we have to offer for their service.
Walked thru Ulven Forging today. Family owned business with 178 great employees where they forge the "Scotty Cameron" putter.
This am I sat down w/PANCAN members to disc the effects of pancreatic cancer & my 	supp of HR 733 the Pancreatic Cancer Research & Edu Act.
Enjoyed meeting w/ members of the Salem Rotary this afternoon to discuss our fiscal 	future, local issues & the budget crisis back in DC.
This am I had the opp to speak @ the Keizer Transit Center groundbreaking. It's a great project & will improve service & access to transit.
This is huge econ news for the Willamette Valley. Will reduce traffic, allow biz to enhance commerce and create long term job & growth opp.
Good luck to all of our Oregon athletes competing on behalf of our great country in the 2012 #London #Olympics. Your hard work will pay off!
My heart goes out to the victims, their families and all Coloradans today following the awful tragedy in Aurora.
#FF Oregon Dems @RepBonamici @WydenPress @RonWyden @SenJeffMerkley @BlumenauerMedia @RepPeterDeFazio

text: I'll be on the floor shortly to talk about the need for Dept of Defense to be as dedicated to federal deficit reduction as everyone else.

I am going to be on @LarsLarsonShow on
101 FM KXL here in a minute to talk about the Farm Bill and SNAP. Tune in and give me some feedback!
Our military leaders have said the biggest threat to national security is not a military one, but a fiscal threat driven by debt & deficits.
House must move forward. Reduce the deficit, strengthen economy to boost investor confidence and create good, US jobs to compete globally.
The House Majority will vote to repeal the health care law for the 31st time today, while Oregonians are still wondering where are the jobs?
Just finished visiting seniors at Pheasant Pointe. I had a great visit with folks and enjoyed updating them on my work in Washington.
After touring the Buckeroo Mayor Clarke & I stopped by OR Mortgage, Wild Bill's Gun Shop & Jasper's to meet w/sb owners in Molalla.
Took a "behind the scenes" tour of the Molalla Buckeroo w/ Tim.  It's been an OR tradition since 1913 & is one of my favorites
Enjoyed lunch w/ members of the Clackamas Rotary @ the Old Spaghetti Factory. It was a great opp to disc local issues & our fiscal future.
Met w/ OSBC members in Keizer & had a great disc w/ folks on ways we can increase access to capital & cut through unnecessary red tape.
Met w/ folks this am to disc the hazards of tsunami debris & identified steps moving forward to help ensure the safety of our nav channels.
I applaud trans reauthorization by Congress. Gives OR rural communs, undergrads and transportation biz certainty to plan for success.
There was no proof of any impropriety by AG Eric Holder. While he has not been a proponent of gun rights, Amer ppl deserve a better process.
Tune into @MarkandDave on KEX1190 now to hear my reaction to the #SCOTUS decision upholding the Affordable Care Act.
Would affect 120K Oregon undergrads on an average of an extra $1K/yr. Congress must act for our young folks to have an affordable uni edu.
Only 4 leg days left until federal student loan interest rates double to 6.8% for Oregon undergrads and their families. #DontDoubleMyRate
Visited Skylane Farms in Woodburn this afternoon & had a great disc w/ folks about the upcoming farm bill and egg legislation.
Just left the WFCA Seminar, where I had an opp to talk to folks about the O&C Trust, Conservation Jobs Act & its importance to rural OR.
Today I met w/ a # of folks to talk about the farm bill. Looking forward to sharing the thoughts of Oregon's small farmers w/ my colleagues.
Stopped by the Idanha Post Office this pm & had a great disc w/ its Postmaster on things we can do to save our rural post offices.
Went on a sb walking tour in Stayton this am & heard some great ideas on how we can help our small businesses create the jobs we need.
Toured Mastercraft furniture's fac in Stayton. The co. employs nearly 140 Oregonians & is looking to add to its workforce in the future.
Met w/ local leaders at Stayton's Commissioners Breakfast this am to disc local issues & update them on what's happening in Washington.
Meeting w/groups this wk to disc farm bill. Met w/a few folks today & gained valuable insights that will help me advocate for OR ag in DC.
Congrats 2 Port of Tillamook Bay on the opening of the Warehouse Business Park. These alt projects mean jobs & econ opportunity 4 our coast.

Good convo w @KPOJCarl abt need for more bipartisanship in #Congress. We need 2 focus on solutions, not ideology. Oregonians expect results!
Talked to @1190KEX this AM about #NoBudgetNoPay. If Congress cant pass a budget, we don't deserve paychecks from hardworking Americans tax $
#IdRatherHave a balanced Fed budget with money 2 invest in domestic programs, than be in debt, do nothing, still get paid. #NoBudgetNoPay

Nice 2 C #Senate pass Ex-Im Bank Reauth to give certainty to US biz & avert unnecessary political brinksmanship in #Congress. Bravo!

Just leaving Camp Withycombe where I toured the 41 Division Armed Forces Reserve Center.
At press conference with Gov to announce $1.9 billion for improving health care coordination in OR. Very exciting news!
Just toured Dave's Killer Bread's facility. Dave's employs more than 240 employees & bakes organic & high quality whole grain breads.
Finished touring Bob's Red Mill w/Bob. Bob's has a great Milwaukie facility, employs 250 & specializes in dairy & casein free products.
Just toured Blount Int'l Inc. The co. manufactures & markets replacement parts & equip. for our forestry & ag markets just to name a few.
Met w/ students that entered this year's art comp. There's a lot of artistic talent in our district. Thanks to everyone that participated.
Hosted small business lunch w/ chamber members from Marion, Polk & Benton Co. Imprt to make things easier so OR businesses can create jobs.
Spoke to students @ McNary HS. We need to extend the reduced rate for Fed Dir Stafford Loans to give them the tools they need to succeed.
Hosted small business lunch w/ members of the Clack. Co. chambers. Disc. the econ & issues affecting small businesses here in OR.
Attended NW OR Labor Council breakfast this am to update members on my work in DC. Great opp. to get feedback & disc. important issues.
Toured Elk Creek Forest Products site in Independence this afternoon. Great co. w/ the potential to bring a lot of jobs to the area.
Spoke to seniors @ Dallas Retirement Village today. Great opp. to hear from seniors on important issues & took a lot of great questions.
Toured Cubanisimo Vineyards w/ Dr. Mauricio Collada & his wife Debra. I'm hoping it will be another great year for our vineyards.
Disc. the fed budget w/ folks at W.Salem Rotary. It's imprt that we work together to find real solutions to get our fiscal house in order.

Just met w/ the Tillamook Co. Creamery Assoc. Board of Dir. to disc. the farm bill; great opp. to hear their thoughts on what's important.

Just leaving my comm. leaders roundtable in Lincoln Co. It was a great opportunity to hear our leaders' fed priorities & answer questions.
Meeting w/ local fishermen to discuss important issues; looking forward to a great discussion & am pleased to be joined by NOAAs Barry Thom.

Just spoke at AFRC's 2012 Meeting. It's important that we practice sustainable mgmt on fed forest lands to generate revenue for rural comm.
